weaver!—pause!—one word!—whither flows the fabric? what palace may it 
deck? wherefore all these ceaseless toilings? Speak, weaver!—stay thy 
hand!—but one single word with thee! Nay—the shuttle flies—the figures 
float from forth the loom; the freshet-rushing carpet for ever slides away. The 
weaver-god, he weaves; and by that weaving is he deafened, that he hears no 
